channel.title: Model Grabber. Bet you cant figure it out
channel.description:
Ok, when i run the model grabber i get this error: [code] Exporting New Cache Files.
Runescape Cache Exporter 3.0 -/- (C) 2008 Troy Osborne (defyboy) -/- -------------------------------- The sprite extracter thingy was by Miss Silabsoft (EWW) -------------------------------- Things added in This Version: Fixed Some of the broken rules A Easier Names parser Sprite Dumper (old Engine Cache) -------------------------------- Parsing Rules... java.io.FileNotFoundException: C:\WINDOWS\.jagex_cache_32\runescape\main_file_ca che.dat2 (The system cannot find the path specified) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.open(Native Method) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at cacheexport2.Main.ProcessRules(Main.java:141) at cacheexport2.Main.main(Main.java:36) Read Error: C:/WINDOWS/.jagex_cache_32/runescape/main_file_cache.idx0 Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NullPointerException at cacheexport2.CacheFile.<init>(CacheFile.java:19) at cacheexport2.Main.ProcessRules(Main.java:149) at cacheexport2.Main.main(Main.java:36)
Press any key to continue . . .
[/code] I even went to runescape and let it load the title screen two times...ANY HELP?
